    • Constructor Detail

      • PrintJobJson

        public PrintJobJson(int newPrinterId,
                    java.lang.String newTitle,
                    java.lang.String newContentType,
                    java.lang.String newContent,
                    java.lang.String newSource)
             throws java.io.IOException
        Creates an object to be serialized into JSON. Requires a contentType - if contentType is base_64, it is encoded into base64.
        Parameters:
        newPrinterId - id of the printer which wil run the PrintJob.
        newTitle - title of the PrintJob.
        newContentType - Type of content. base64, uri, etc.
        newContent - either a file, or a URL to a file. Depends on contentType.
        newSource - Would be from the PrintNode-Java client.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if "xxx_base64" is selected as content-type and the file specified in content does not exist.
